From: Micheal Waltz <micheal@ecliptik.com>
Date: Mon, 27 Apr 2026 09:51:03 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?[DOSKUTSU]=20dos:=20Phase=209=20wave=207=20patc?=
 =?UTF-8?q?h=200020=20=E2=80=94=20gate=20use=5Flfb=20on=20force=5Fbanked?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=5Fpath=20+=20reduce=20GetWindowSurface=20log=20spam?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Wave 6 cirrus6 capture confirmed Patch 0019's auto-detection fired
correctly on real Cirrus + UNIVBE 6.70, but the screen was completely
blank (not even Loading text). Root cause: patch 0019 only flipped the
FB-LAYER path while leaving the BIOS in LFB mode -- mismatch. The BIOS
programs the LFB hardware path; our FB layer writes through the banked
window at A000:0; the BIOS never set up that window for display refresh
because we asked for LFB. cirrus6 SDLDBG line 8 confirmed this:
mode-set #1 reports use_lfb=1 banked=0 but CreateWindowFramebuffer
exits with use_dosmemput=1 vram_phys=0x000a0000 -- two layers
disagreeing.

  * SDL_dosmodes.c DOSVESA_SetDisplayMode: gate use_lfb decision on
    !(data->force_banked_path || SDL_HINT_DOS_DISABLE_LFB). When forced,
    VBE 0x4F02 is called WITHOUT the 0x4000 LFB bit, BIOS programs
    banked-mode hardware path, our FB layer's banked dosmemput aligns
    with what the BIOS set up. Cirrus auto-detect AND manual env hint
    both work end-to-end now.

  * SDL_video.c SDL_GetWindowSurface: gate the per-call log to first
    5 + every 1000th for the cached-return path (which is hit by every
    drawcall via Renderer's fast-path SDL_GetWindowSurface call).
    cirrus6 had 43,244 lines of GetWindowSurface log spam, fsync-per-line
    on CF storage. The recreate-path branch (rare, lifecycle-relevant)
    keeps logging every call. DOSBox-X smoke confirms 77 total lines vs
    the prior 43,000+.

DOSBox-X smoke (cirrus auto-detect doesn't fire on emulator vendor
'DOSBox Development Team') confirms LFB path still engages cleanly --
no regression on Mach64 / DOSBox-X targets, only behavior change is
on detected Cirrus or hint-forced builds.
---
 src/video/SDL_video.c        | 24 +++++++++++++++++++-----
 src/video/dos/SDL_dosmodes.c | 13 +++++++++++++
 2 files changed, 32 insertions(+), 5 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/video/SDL_video.c b/src/video/SDL_video.c
index 14cf0fb35..8b45af4e6 100644
--- a/src/video/SDL_video.c
+++ b/src/video/SDL_video.c
@@ -3699,11 +3699,25 @@ SDL_Surface *SDL_GetWindowSurface(SDL_Window *window)
 {
     CHECK_WINDOW_MAGIC(window, NULL);
 
-    DOSKUTSU_LIFECYCLE_LOG("GetWindowSurface: window=%p surface_valid=%d existing=%p (will %s)\n",
-                           (void *)window, (int)window->surface_valid,
-                           (void *)window->surface,
-                           window->surface_valid ? "return cached" : "destroy+recreate");
-    if (!window->surface_valid) {
+    // DOSKUTSU patch 0020 (Phase 9 wave 7): the cached-return path is hit
+    // every drawcall by Renderer::drawSurface (~340 calls/flip × 100 flips =
+    // 34000+ entries per session). Patch 0008 logs unconditionally with a
+    // per-line fsync; on CF-card storage that's milliseconds of disk wait
+    // per call. cirrus6 SDLDBG.LOG showed 43,244 GetWindowSurface lines in
+    // one 5-minute run -- a substantial fraction of the per-flip 150 ms
+    // "render_present" cost. Sample the cached path (first 5 + every 1000th)
+    // while keeping every recreate-path call logged (those are rare and
+    // matter for lifecycle attribution).
+    static unsigned long _gws_cached_calls = 0;
+    if (window->surface_valid) {
+        ++_gws_cached_calls;
+        if (_gws_cached_calls <= 5 || (_gws_cached_calls % 1000) == 0) {
+            DOSKUTSU_LIFECYCLE_LOG("GetWindowSurface (cached) #%lu: window=%p existing=%p\n",
+                                   _gws_cached_calls, (void *)window, (void *)window->surface);
+        }
+    } else {
+        DOSKUTSU_LIFECYCLE_LOG("GetWindowSurface: window=%p surface_valid=0 existing=%p (will destroy+recreate)\n",
+                               (void *)window, (void *)window->surface);
         if (window->surface) {
             window->surface->internal_flags &= ~SDL_INTERNAL_SURFACE_DONTFREE;
             SDL_DestroySurface(window->surface);
diff --git a/src/video/dos/SDL_dosmodes.c b/src/video/dos/SDL_dosmodes.c
index 00b34a2e1..c7cc9eb04 100644
--- a/src/video/dos/SDL_dosmodes.c
+++ b/src/video/dos/SDL_dosmodes.c
@@ -824,7 +824,20 @@ bool DOSVESA_SetDisplayMode(SDL_VideoDevice *device, SDL_VideoDisplay *sdl_displ
                                   (modedata->win_a_attributes & VBE_WINATTR_USABLE) == VBE_WINATTR_USABLE;
     const bool hint_allow_direct = SDL_GetHintBoolean(SDL_HINT_DOS_ALLOW_DIRECT_FRAMEBUFFER, false);
     const bool hint_prefer_lfb = SDL_GetHintBoolean(SDL_HINT_DOS_PREFER_LFB, false);
+
+    // DOSKUTSU patch 0020 (Phase 9 wave 7): when force_banked is set --
+    // either the Cirrus auto-detect from patch 0019, OR the manual
+    // SDL_HINT_DOS_DISABLE_LFB env var -- the VBE BIOS must be told to set
+    // the BANKED mode, not LFB. Patch 0019 only flipped the FB-LAYER path
+    // while leaving the BIOS in LFB mode -- mismatch: BIOS programs LFB
+    // hardware path, FB layer writes through the banked window at A000:0,
+    // BIOS hasn't set up that window for display refresh, no visual on
+    // real Cirrus (cirrus6 capture symptom). Gating use_lfb on
+    // !force_banked here keeps both layers in sync.
+    const bool hint_disable_lfb = SDL_GetHintBoolean(SDL_HINT_DOS_DISABLE_LFB, false);
+    const bool force_banked = (data->force_banked_path || hint_disable_lfb) && is_banked_usable;
     const bool use_lfb = modedata->has_lfb &&
+                         !force_banked &&
                          (hint_prefer_lfb ||
                           !is_banked_usable ||
                           !hint_allow_direct);
